{
  "stem": "16930.2",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 305.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I said, why?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He says, you're a shegetz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I said, Yossi, how did I get to be a shegetz?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He said, I heard you went to-- to [INAUDIBLE] [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Akiva ?] camp this summer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So [INAUDIBLE] the same week.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I was kind of an ignorant, innocent kind of kid.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I said to myself, how is it possible within a couple of days to be both a shegetz and a religious fanatic?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I didn't understand then what I now know the nature of lashon hara.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Do you know what lashon hara means?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Lashon hara means thing-- evil things about others, sort of gossip about others.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And lashon hara always contains within it an element of [HEBREW], needless hate.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, I wasn't aware of it at that time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I'm quite well aware of lashon hara and [HEBREW], so I understand it now, what was going on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And everybody wants to be an insider.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when you're an insider, you must have outsiders.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This worked not only for the Nazis, who had to have Jews as outsiders, but also works among Jews to-- in their groups, with insiders of their groups, and have the others as outsiders.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I didn't fit.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so this guy was [INAUDIBLE] I was going to the [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Akiva. ?] That made me a shegetz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the word shegetz comes from sheketz-- sheketz [HEBREW], the abomination of idol worship.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's not just a nice name, shegetz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that kid was using it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And fanatic?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A religious fanatic for not being willing to eat non-kosher food, treif meat?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I-- so I don't think that either things were justified.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
